Required:

- Support '--opt=ARG' syntax
- Support grouping options in --help output
- Support per-group banners in --help output
- Support '--' terminator for flag parsing
- Tests for:
-- Short opt parsing
-- Long opt parsing
-- Opt with arg parsing (optional, required, =ARG syntax)
-- '--' terminator
-- '--help' output
-- Overriding default '-h' arg
- Intro docs

Nice to have?
- Positional args (see http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_54_0/doc/html/program_options/tutorial.html)
- Args hidden from --help output
- Support for --version output

For comparison:

- Boost Program Options: http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_54_0/doc/html/program_options/tutorial.html
- Ruby OptionParser: http://ruby-doc.org/stdlib-2.0/libdoc/optparse/rdoc/OptionParser.html
- Go flag package: http://golang.org/pkg/flag/
- libc getopt: http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Getopt.html
